        <abstract> 
<p>Gives CD a reference to one of his papers ["Remarks on the modes of variation of nearly affined species or races of birds", <hi rend="italic">J. Asiat. Soc. Bengal</hi> 19 (1850): 221–9]</p> 
            <p>and discusses moulting in birds.</p>
            <p>Quotes instance of an action by an elephant that apparently displays considerable intelligence.</p>
        </abstract>
